---------- IF WANT TO USE UBUNTU FOR YOUR SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT ---------------
1. Download Ubuntu for your System from Official site/Windows from CD.
https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop

2. Use Balena Etcher for burning your images on Pendrive.
https://www.balena.io/etcher/
If pendrive doesn't work as normal pendrive even after formatting, search How to format pendrive using CMD in windows.
Open cmd as administrator & type
> diskpart
> list disk
This should list all the disks, replace x by your number of pendrive.
> select disk x
> clean
> create partition primary
Now, you should your pendrive as 1 unit, Quick format it by NTFS and assign any letter by opening Format Disk in search on toolbar,
if it doesn't work, type
> format fs=ntfs
> assign

You are ready to install Ubuntu,



Install Wireless USB Adaptor drivers of u

3. Install VS Code from Ubuntu Software if using Ubuntu and enable extensions like live-server, code formatter, etc..

4. Install Node/npm from official source.
https://nodejs.org/en/download/
If using Ubuntu, Open terminal
> sudo apt update
> sudo apt install nodejs
> sudo apt install npm
> nodejs -v
If you see your version, installation was successful.
> npm -v
If you see your version, installation was successful.
If you face problems, see full Guide
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-node-js-on-ubuntu-18-04

5. Install mongodb using the Guide.
https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-windows/
Direct download link-> https://www.mongodb.com/download-center/community?jmp=docs
To run the MongoDB service :- 
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.2\bin\mongo.exe"

6. Install Git and learn basic commands of git to use github.

7. Install Postman from the link.
https://www.getpostman.com/downloads/

